<br>
I guess I have to say that Relient K writing about relationships and things not directly related to faith gives almost a stronger witness than the Newsboys, because you hear their songs together and it helps dispell the misconception that every person of faith is some sort of perfect pure goody-two-shoes who's in a completely separate universe.<br>
<br>
It makes you feel so much closer to Relient K when they're singing about cell phone minutes and not understanding their girlfriends and bad college experiences, and then you hear them singing to God about how he's the only one who understands them, and how they keep screwing up and turning away from him... &quot;It's my... my trademark move, to turn my back on You.  It's my... my trademark move, to realize I should improve.  And sometime, soon after that, You'll see me come crawling back.&quot;  And it really makes you think, hey, there are normal people with normal problems and feelings who are totally into God...  God isn't an alien thing, it's part of real life... I can be normal and still be Christian... wow!<br>
<br>
But the Newsboys are awesome too, if you want the completely Christian-themed music experience... they're a lot better for worship music than Relient K.  But I daresay probably a lot more teens have been introduced to God by Relient K than Newsboys, because they can't relate as well to Newsboys.  But again, I love both for their unique styles, so *shrug* who knows?  Creed does not consider themselves a Christian band but they definitely write some religious themes in their songs... I guess a Christian band is defined by what the artists want to be defined as, how much they're willing to be termed &quot;Christian&quot; and worship and sing about God in their music.  You wouldn't know Relient K was Christian by listening to a couple of their songs, but then you hear their other songs that are very heavily Christian-themed, just like you don't know if somebody's Christian by knowing them for a couple days, but then you get to talking about God and you realize they have a lot of faith.<br>
<br>
