I have never had that impression of people who write about their faith directly.  And I don't know, but that one song (and I have no idea who sings it because we've just sung it in church) where the singer sings, &quot;Sometimes at night when I am afraid.  I cover my eyes, cover my shame.  'Cause here in the dark, I'm torn apart.  So come with Your light and fill up my heart.  Oh great light of the world, fill up my soul.  I'm half a man here, so come make me whole.&quot;  (Or as we sing in church, &quot;I'll never mend here.&quot;)  The song is relational - talking about the relationship between the singer and God and you can't say the guy sounds like he's a perfect goody-two-shoes.  His words make it clear that he's not.<br>
